# Quantum Bridge Server Commands

## Start Server (gold standard)
```bash
cd /Users/tref/uvspeed && uv run uvspeed_cli.py serve
```

## CLI Tools (always use uv run)
```bash
uv run uvspeed_cli.py classify myfile.py     # Classify with prefixes
uv run uvspeed_cli.py prefix src/lib.rs      # Add prefix gutter
uv run uvspeed_cli.py stats *.py --json      # Prefix distribution
uv run uvspeed_cli.py pre                    # Pre-push checklist
uv run uvspeed_cli.py health                 # Check bridge server
uv run uvspeed_cli.py version                # Version info
```

## API Endpoints (when bridge is running on :8085)
```bash
# Prefix code
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8085/api/prefix \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"code": "CODE_HERE", "language": "python"}'

# Security scan
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8085/api/security/scan \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"directory": "."}'

# Git hook install
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8085/api/git/hook/install \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"repo": "."}'

# PR diff report
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8085/api/git/diff-report \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"old": "OLD", "new": "NEW", "language": "python", "filename": "file.py"}'

# Roadmap scan
curl -s -X POST http://localhost:8085/api/roadmap/scan \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"directory": "."}'
```

